<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-E5B8292A-7DC5-434F-A78B-2C9D13902D1E" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-E5B8292A-7DC5-434F-A78B-2C9D13902D1E" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to get the trace files</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-9C631935-A322-4774-A553-6D0B52308454"><p class="- topic/p ">Trace data are extended log files which can be analyzed by R&amp;D. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> They have to be collected by Service every time an issue cannot be fixed or cannot be reproduced and assistance for troubleshooting is required. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-BD13EB05-ECF9-4C06-9D86-8AB9C82D2DE9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Choose the correct procedure</title><p class="- topic/p "> There are 4 procedures to retrieve the trace files : 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">2 On site procedures: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- On site procedure with Settings Editor 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- On site procedure via the engine USB port 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">2 Back office procedures: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Back office procedure 1 via ORS 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Back office procedure 2 via ORS Remote Assistance VPN 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-0B2C7E1F-C780-4F39-83CE-384DBC2235D7" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">On site procedure with Settings Editor</title><note id="GUID-9D56B893-7CAE-4601-AFB7-6917DB94A55E" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">This procedure requires "system administrator" rights on the printer. 
</p></note><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-DDFF6F7E-CEA4-4B5F-9AC7-0288D2C24DDD" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the Settings Editor 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Browse to: Support &gt; Troubleshooting &gt; Create and download logging and reports: 
</p><fig id="GUID-BEB80A82-5BDB-4A5F-A648-A36A2E96E2E3" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FE3C67F4-28BE-4FC8-B05B-40FC1498A2F5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FE3C67F4-28BE-4FC8-B05B-40FC1498A2F5-low.png"/><image href="GUID-173E12D5-407E-4506-894A-07EBD39C3450-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-173E12D5-407E-4506-894A-07EBD39C3450-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> In the right hand column click on : (depending on the release:) "Create ZIP files with loggings" or "Create trace file" or "Create log file with report / trace files". 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> As a reference: a trace file is always larger than 25MB and can be up to 1 GB. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The System Administrator window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-F14A7EF9-0897-4D6F-B711-8682836D6361" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4A83672E-8EBF-40CC-A9BA-E7A631C8A65C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4A83672E-8EBF-40CC-A9BA-E7A631C8A65C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Login as a System Administrator. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The Log file with report/trace files (create and download) window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-57DA3A1D-610F-4C98-9228-86414BF577CF" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-CF065584-7289-4C73-9ABD-8304ADD449C5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CF065584-7289-4C73-9ABD-8304ADD449C5-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> A list of already created trace files is shown below the button. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Some errors automatically generate a trace file. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The trace you need may already be in this list. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The name contains the error code when generated by an error and always contains, a date and time at the end. 
</p><note id="GUID-B72DE31E-6056-4547-9093-2918402B1465" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">It is possible that this windows show older trace files. 
</p></note></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Create log file with report/trace files. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After a variable time, the following window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-997066C5-E660-4AE2-8960-42B06973A697" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-2F31B730-3876-44DA-BEED-3512688ADF0A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2F31B730-3876-44DA-BEED-3512688ADF0A-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click the name of the trace file that you want to retrieve. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following message displays at the bottom of the browser window: 
</p><fig id="GUID-9829423F-C095-4A0F-BDB4-75DB0781A0CF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-11C3AF22-BF18-49C2-96F4-EFC918298C8C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-11C3AF22-BF18-49C2-96F4-EFC918298C8C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Select ‘Save as’ and store the trace file at a convenient location. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-CE63937B-86B3-458A-B150-B4216E005BB4" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">On site procedure via the engine USB port</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-008129BF-FEC4-4132-AD01-BF9EA40913FB" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Insert the USB key into the USB port of the printer below the user interface. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to "System" &gt; "Service" and press the button "Export diagnostic to USB". 
</p><fig id="GUID-90BA0F1F-4781-4A51-AD77-BCF25FBF9FD7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-24983982-F4C9-413C-9C28-C23108A0BB12-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-24983982-F4C9-413C-9C28-C23108A0BB12-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Enter the administrator password when requested. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">This will create a file in the root of the USB key: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">&lt;system_name&gt;_TraceData_&lt;date&gt;_&lt;time&gt;.zip 
</p></li></ul></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-927D8150-DC01-4AAE-ADD7-1BBAA576B164" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Back office procedure 1 via ORS</title><note id="GUID-591AF1EC-9E7F-4057-9319-E5D24C42C6DE" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> In practice the file size of the data dump file often exceeds 300 MB. Than the trace data will be not be present in the data dump. In this case proceed to back office procedure 2. 
</p></note><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-FECA7A75-12AF-4F00-A7C2-75CDD9DD6C6C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Connect to the ORS portal (<xref href="https://service.cpp.canon" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://service.cpp.canon</xref>). 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Find the printer in Search Configurations. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In the Configuration details, select Diagnostic data &gt; Worklist. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Request the diagnostics data dump from the device by clicking the “I” icon: 
</p><fig id="GUID-139CB793-3F7C-4FEC-84F7-109753833E38" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2684ED00-A278-44BC-A3B9-EECB561AEA4C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2684ED00-A278-44BC-A3B9-EECB561AEA4C-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> The following message displays and the "I" icon becomes greyed out: 
</p><fig id="GUID-DED13748-FA81-4914-8425-4665AC8EC5FE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5758F9A7-33E0-4CC3-9339-35E65152699B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5758F9A7-33E0-4CC3-9339-35E65152699B-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Click "Ok". 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">After a short time, the diagnostic data dump is available ( “I” icon not greyed out anymore). 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Download it by clicking the Download diagnostic data icon: 
</p><fig id="GUID-A8FDE056-7DEE-4827-8F09-095062D447E6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8F4E51D9-3006-4706-B4BF-2EAA3D52CC46-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8F4E51D9-3006-4706-B4BF-2EAA3D52CC46-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The file is downloaded to the default download locationof your browser. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Open the diagnostic data dump file with for example 7-Zip: 
</p><fig id="GUID-6D9BC803-FB11-4893-AE99-A1ABC0868F9E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C69C6B32-337C-462D-8833-AAF1A18F23A9-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C69C6B32-337C-462D-8833-AAF1A18F23A9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Extract the datalog.xml file from the zip file. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-17DA2CC9-CDA6-4F57-9664-0065564111A6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Back office procedure 2 via ORS Remote Assistance VPN</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-955C6D22-EFBA-4DA8-8BFA-C2E97A99D88B" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Connect to the ORS portal (<xref href="https://service.cpp.canon" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://service.cpp.canon</xref>). 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Find the printer in Search Configurations. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Ask the customer to enable Remote Assistance. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> In the Remote data tab select VPN. 
</p><fig id="GUID-3F3EAC26-1B2D-4B57-8BDB-9D0781509253" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B5B69699-3864-4778-8D78-6CD41AB0065E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B5B69699-3864-4778-8D78-6CD41AB0065E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Select the double arrow symbol. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The Remote Assistance download window opens. 
</p><fig id="GUID-3057EA4A-F81C-4380-AA16-BD8C0BA6E3CF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C236C35C-9CBD-4C01-9EA6-A1A51246F629-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C236C35C-9CBD-4C01-9EA6-A1A51246F629-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Select this window. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The login screen opens. 
</p><fig id="GUID-A15C83FD-E30F-4980-9EDA-13EC1FF01114" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2962FD5B-6F11-4E6C-8BC3-98ACCE90D9B8-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2962FD5B-6F11-4E6C-8BC3-98ACCE90D9B8-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Fill in the password. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The VPN window opens. 
</p><fig id="GUID-3C36BB07-6182-40B4-BB5A-57974170E6EE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AE36A048-6159-4F56-836C-E2E324C5940A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AE36A048-6159-4F56-836C-E2E324C5940A-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Copy the IP of Partner address. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Open a browser window. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Copy the address in the search bar. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The Settings Editor opens. 
</p><fig id="GUID-01CA937E-55C6-4761-BDE6-5821BAFAAB70" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0C03055A-D566-4928-A40A-61291083C3A8-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0C03055A-D566-4928-A40A-61291083C3A8-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Proceed as described in On Site Procedure. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-5C937DF0-2BDD-497B-B1AC-3013A8804D24.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>